<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="although-conj">although <strong><em>conj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /ɔːl'ðəʊ/    美 /ɔːl'ðoʊ/  </p>
<p>[引导让步状语从句， 用法同though]</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>尽管；虽然：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Although the job takes a signiﬁcant amount of time, most students agree that the experience is worth it.
尽管这份工作会花大量的时间，但是大部分学生都认为这个经历是值得的。</p><footer>2015 湖南</footer></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>然而；但是：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I don’t believe we’ve met before, although I must say you do look familiar.
我想我们以前没见过，不过我得说你看上去的确面熟。</p><footer>2012 全国</footer></div>

<p>注: although不与but连用，但可以与yet, still等表转折的副词连用。  </p>
<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li><strong><em>_</em></strong> (尽管) birds use their feathers for ﬂight, some of their feathers are for other purposes.  （2017 北京改）  </li>
<li><strong><em>_</em></strong>_ small, the company has about 1,000 buyers in over 30 countries.  （2013 天津）<br />
A.As<br />
B.If<br />
C.Although<br />
D.Once  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. Although / Though  2. C  </p></div>